 🌍 SafeZone Hub - Kenya

A Real-Time Disaster Alert & Safety Resource Single Page Application**

SafeZone Hub is a modern, user-friendly web application designed to help Kenyans stay safe during natural disasters and emergencies. It provides live disaster alerts, weather forecasts with rain warnings, nearest emergency resources, and important hotlines — all in one interactive dashboard.

 Features

- Live Location Tracking – Works anywhere in Kenya using browser geolocation
- Interactive Map – Powered by Leaflet.js with disaster markers
- Real-time Weather – Current conditions + 3-day rain forecast with weather alerts
- Nearby Resources – Hospitals, shelters, and water points sorted by distance with county names
- Disaster Alerts – Fetched from GDACS API, filtered for Kenya
- Kenya Emergency Hotlines – Quick access to 999, 112, Kenya Red Cross, and more
- Responsive Design – Clean UI with dark mode support
- Auto-refresh – Updates alerts and weather every 6 minutes

 Technologies Used

- HTML5, CSS3 & JavaScript (Single Page Application)
- Leaflet.js – Interactive mapping
- GDACS API – Global disaster alerts
- Open-Meteo API – Weather data and forecasts
- Fetch API – For making asynchronous requests
- Geolocation API – Live user location

 How to Use

1. Clone or download the project
2. Open `index.html` in your browser (or use Live Server in VS Code)
3. Click "Enable Live Location Tracking" to get personalized results
4. Search for specific alerts using keywords like `flood`, `drought`, or `Nairobi`
5. View nearest resources with distances and county names
6. Check weather alerts and emergency hotlines

